# Lint vs Validate

**"Lint" / "format" / "style check"** → Apply **@.cursor/rules/lint-rules.mdc**:
- Scan for style violations (tables, naming, WoW string functions, semicolons, etc.)
- Report and optionally fix violations
- Do NOT use validate_lua.py for this

**"Validate" / "syntax check"** → Run **Scripts/validate_lua.py**:
- Lua 5.1 syntax validation via luac
- See @.cursor/rules/lua-validation.mdc

**"Full lint check" / "pre-push check"** → Do BOTH:
1. Apply lint-rules.mdc (style)
2. Run `python Scripts/validate_lua.py` (syntax)
